reviews.text: Good place to relax, comfort environment
I like the comfortable atmosphere in Starbucks Coffee, for Hong Kong the coffee is quite good and the food too.

Afternoon tea at this Starbucks, location amid central CBD, easy to approach from all directions in this area. We ordered two drinks and a chest cake yet the shop itself was rather small making you feel congested. F and B was the same akin to other outlets, if you can get a window seat facing the street would be good, otherwise, be prepared to share the limited space inside. This is a good stop for a drink whilst if you want to relax inside a cafe, I would recommend you seek for other locations.
Good services
Best place to hang out.
